`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Why a central registration module matters:** Without it, systems are called ad-hoc from scattered `useFrame` hooks and React effects — making execution order unpredictable and debugging impossible. The registration module is the **manifest** of all game logic: one glance shows every system that runs per tick, what phase it belongs to, and how its signature is adapted. This is the foundation for profiling (which phase is slow?), debugging (which system broke?), and feature flags (disable combat for peaceful testing).
